<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,350,518]" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">
The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[274,393,350,374]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Radiarctia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[274,393,350,374]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">Radiarctia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was established by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dubatolov" box="[618,818,350,374]" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" refString="Dubatolov, V. V. (2006) New genera and species of Arctiinae from the Afrotropical fauna (Lepidoptera: Arctiidae). Nachrichten des Entomologische Vereins Apollo, 27 (3), 139 - 152." type="journal article" year="2006">
Dubatolov (
<number box="[751,810,350,374]" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" value="2006.0">2006</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
for four Afrotropical 
<taxonomicName box="[1064,1168,350,374]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Arctiinae</taxonomicName>
formerly placed in 
<taxonomicName authority="Curtis (1825)" authorityName="Curtis" authorityYear="1825" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Spilosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">Spilosoma</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Curtis" box="[240,395,386,410]" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" refString="Curtis, J. (1825) British Entomology. London, 2, 98 plates + text." type="book" year="1825">
Curtis (
<number box="[325,386,386,410]" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" value="1825.0">1825</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[406,525,387,411]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Radiarctia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[406,525,387,411]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">Radiarctia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are comparatively robust with distinct interneural patches or stripes. The valvae are wide and mostly bifurcate apically and the vesicae display distinct groups of pin-like cornuti; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dubatolov" box="[1236,1436,422,446]" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" refString="Dubatolov, V. V. (2006) New genera and species of Arctiinae from the Afrotropical fauna (Lepidoptera: Arctiidae). Nachrichten des Entomologische Vereins Apollo, 27 (3), 139 - 152." type="journal article" year="2006">
Dubatolov (
<number box="[1369,1428,422,446]" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" value="2006.0">2006</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
considered this character autapomorphic for the genus. As old, worn or faded specimens of mostly 
<taxonomicName box="[1262,1394,459,483]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Radiarctia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="screabile">
<emphasis box="[1262,1394,459,483]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">R. screabile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are frequently misidentified in collections (see Introduction), 
<taxonomicName box="[798,900,494,518]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Radiarctia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="screabile">
<emphasis box="[798,900,494,518]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">screabile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is redescribed in full below.
</paragraph>
